constructor.name: editor
constructor.description: Component displaying the correct editor for an attribute. It is possible to specify the editor type to use. If not specified, it will try to get the correct type on its own.

properties.name: debug
properties.description: whether the UI is in debug mode or not

properties.name: content
properties.description: the attribute which information is displayed and that can be edited with the editor.

properties.name: description
properties.description: Computed property, binded to the description of the attribute

properties.name: editorType
properties.description: finds the correct template name for the editor

functions.name: actions_inspect
functions.description: inspects the object in the console (see debugUtils for more info)

constructor.name: renderer
constructor.description: Component displaying the correct renderer for an attribute. It is possible to specify the renderer type to use. If not specified, it will try to get the correct type on its own.

functions.name: actions_inspect
functions.description: inspects the object in the console (see debugUtils for more info)

functions.name: actions_do
functions.description: sends an action to the parent controller. Every parameter after the first one is bubbled to the parent controller action

properties.name: debug
properties.description: whether the UI is in debug mode or not

functions.name: doAction
functions.description: send an action to the default target (usually ApplicationController instance)

functions.name: startOfTheDay
functions.description: Computes for a timestamp the timestamp at midnight of it's day. the computation day from timestamp depends on if a timestamp is given. when given start of the day is computed from timestamp, otherwise it is done from now timestamp

functions.name: isToday
functions.description: Boolean value determining wether the given date included in today Value depends on the client clock

functions.name: applyVolatileFilter
functions.description: apply a filter to an element before to transmit it to an other view. see goToInfo method of brick-calendar for example

parameters.name: transition:
parameters.description: promise to transmit the element to an other view

parameters.name: filter:
parameters.description: a mongoDB style query as a string

functions.name: setController
functions.description: Initialize the notification controller when the controller is not set up, it stores all the messages in a buffer stack.

functions.name: children
functions.description: Recursively fetch widgets an returns a list of chilren

functions.name: sideloadItem
functions.description: Sideload a JSON object to the payload

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: The DS.Model class of the item to be sideloaded

parameters.name: item
parameters.description: JSON object representing the record to sideload to the payload

functions.name: extractRelationships
functions.description: Extract relationships from the payload and sideload them. This function recursively walks down the JSON tree

parameters.name: recordJSON
parameters.description: JSON object representing the current record in the payload to look for relationships

parameters.name: primaryType
parameters.description: The DS.Model class of the record object

parameters.name: actionName
parameters.description: Bind a key combination to an action registered in the actionsRegistry.

properties.name: selected_tags
properties.description: list of tags to mute in console

properties.name: colors
properties.description: Whether to use colors or not in the JS console

properties.name: role
properties.description: A role that is assigned to the user
